stylometry: The general management tradeoff and decsion when facing Inventory - is that demand is uncertain. If you purchase too much inventory then you will lose money; reversely if you don't have enough inventory for your customers to purchase you also lose money. Therefore the very broad tradeoff of this is finding the balance in demand; because demand is unknown. A business must realize this factor and ultimately make decisions that will be beneficial towards this company; in this scenario both too much inventory and not enough inventory will lose the business money, when ultimately the goal of a business is to maximize profits. Having the right figures of inventory will help a company do this and will be better in the long run, as well.
